description: Number of active channels.
Sum by status to count channels. Filter by channel and status tags to create notifications.
The datetime at which the queue manager was last altered (MQCA_ALTERATION_DATE, MQCA_ALTERATION_TIME).
The current number of connections to the queue manager (MQIACF_CONNECTION_COUNT).
This indicates whether distribution-list messages can be placed on the queue (MQIA_DIST_LISTS).
The length of the longest message the queue manager can handle (MQIA_MAX_MSG_LENGTH).
Backout threshold used by other applications (MQIA_BACKOUT_THRESHOLD).
The number of messages in the queue (MQIA_CURRENT_Q_DEPTH)
A depth high event has been generated (MQIA_Q_DEPTH_HIGH_EVENT).
The threshold against which the queue depth is compared before generated a queue high event (MQIA_Q_DEPTH_HIGH_LIMIT).
A depth low event has been generated (MQIA_Q_DEPTH_LOW_EVENT).
The low limit on the depth to create an alert (MQIA_Q_DEPTH_LOW_LIMIT).
The max depth of the queue (MQIA_MAX_Q_DEPTH).
Controls whether queue full events are generated (MQIA_Q_DEPTH_MAX_EVENT).
The percent of the queue that is currently utilized.
Number of times a message is retrieved (MQIA_HARDEN_GET_BACKOUT).
Gets are inhibited (MQIA_INHIBIT_GET).
Puts are inhibited (MQIA_INHIBIT_PUT).
The default way to open the queue for input (MQIA_DEF_INPUT_OPEN_OPTION).
The max length of a message (MQIA_MAX_MSG_LENGTH).
The order in which messages will be returned after a get operation
The age of the oldest message on the queue in seconds (MQIA_MSG_DELIVERY_SEQUENCE).
The number of handles currently open (MQIA_OPEN_INPUT_COUNT).
The number of handles that are available for adding messages (MQIA_OPEN_OUTPUT_COUNT).
The default persistance of messages on the queue (MQIA_DEF_PERSISTENCE).
The default priority for messages on the queue (MQIA_DEF_PRIORITY).
The period of time to retain the queue after elapsed it is elegible for deletion (MQIA_RETENTION_INTERVAL).
Controls if the queue exists in a cell directory (MQIA_SCOPE).
The time since last serviced (MQIA_Q_SERVICE_INTERVAL)
Controls whether Service Interval High or Service Interval OK events are generated (MQIA_Q_SERVICE_INTERVAL_EVENT).
Controls if trigger messages are written to an initiation queue (MQIA_TRIGGER_CONTROL).
The number of messages on the queue before a trigger event is written (MQIA_TRIGGER_DEPTH).
The message priority below which a message doesn't generate a trigger message (MQIA_TRIGGER_MSG_PRIORITY).
The conditions under which trigger messages are written as a result of messages arriving on this queue (MQIA_TRIGGER_TYPE).
The type of queue (MQIA_Q_TYPE).
What the queue is used for (MQIA_USAGE).
The number of uncommitted messages on the queue (MQIACF_UNCOMMITTED_MSGS).
Maximum number of messages on a queue (MQIA_HIGH_Q_DEPTH).
Number of messages dequeued (MQIA_MSG_DEQ_COUNT).
Number of messages enqueued (MQIA_MSG_ENQ_COUNT).
Time since statistics reset in seconds (MQIA_TIME_SINCE_RESET).
The datetime at which the channel was last altered (MQCA_ALTERATION_DATE, MQCA_ALTERATION_TIME).
The batch interval in seconds (MQIACH_BATCH_INTERVAL).
The batch size (MQIACH_BATCH_SIZE).
The disconnection interval in seconds (parameter identifier: MQIACH_DISC_INTERVAL).
Heartbeat interval in seconds (parameter identifier: MQIACH_HB_INTERVAL).
KeepAlive interval in seconds (parameter identifier: MQIACH_KEEP_ALIVE_INTERVAL).
Long retry count (parameter identifier: MQIACH_LONG_RETRY).
Long timer (parameter identifier: MQIACH_LONG_TIMER).
Maximum message length (parameter identifier: MQIACH_MAX_MSG_LENGTH).
Message retry count (parameter identifier: MQIACH_MR_COUNT).
Message retry interval in seconds (parameter identifier: MQIACH_MR_INTERVAL).
Network priority (parameter identifier: MQIACH_NETWORK_PRIORITY).
Speed at which non-persistent messages are to be sent (parameter identifier: MQIACH_NPM_SPEED).
Number of sharing conversations (parameter identifier: MQIACH_SHARING_CONVERSATIONS).
Short retry count (parameter identifier: MQIACH_SHORT_RETRY).
Short timer (parameter identifier: MQIACH_SHORT_TIMER).
Number of buffers received (parameter identifier: MQIACH_BUFFERS_RCVD).
Number of buffers sent (parameter identifier: MQIACH_BUFFERS_SENT).
Number of bytes received (parameter identifier: MQIACH_BYTES_RCVD).
Number of bytes sent (parameter identifier: MQIACH_BYTES_SENT).
Channel status (parameter identifier: MQIACH_CHANNEL_STATUS).
MCA status (parameter identifier: MQIACH_MCA_STATUS).
Number of messages sent or received, or number of MQI calls handled (parameter identifier: MQIACH_MSGS).
SSL secret key resets (parameter identifier: MQIACH_SSL_KEY_RESETS).
Number of completed batches (parameter identifier: MQIACH_BATCHES).
Number of messages in-doubt (parameter identifier: MQIACH_CURRENT_MSGS).
Whether the channel is currently in doubt (parameter identifier: MQIACH_INDOUBT_STATUS).
Datetime last message was sent, or MQI call was handled (MQCACH_LAST_MSG_DATE, MQCACH_LAST_MSG_TIME).
